  {
   "id": "panelA_t",
   "type": "text",
   "x": 50,
   "y": 1140,
   "width": 580,
   "height": 450,
   "angle": 0,
   "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
   "backgroundColor": "transparent",
   "fillStyle": "solid",
   "strokeWidth": 2,
   "strokeStyle": "solid",
   "roughness": 1,
   "opacity": 100,
   "groupIds": [],
   "frameId": null,
   "roundness": null,
   "seed": 13938522,
   "version": 1,
   "versionNonce": 1131247331,
   "isDeleted": false,
   "boundElements": [],
   "updated": 1749769200000,
   "link": null,
   "locked": false,
   "text": "INBOUND CALL — LIFECYCLE\n1  caller dials your Twilio number\n2  Twilio POSTs /twilio/voice — S2 signature checked first\n3  caller ID → role → persona (owner: butler · stranger: front desk)\n4  TwiML <Connect><ConversationRelay url=wss://…?token=NONCE>\n5  WS accepted only with a fresh nonce (S9), then text↔text:\n    STT prompt in → brain tokens out → TTS · barge-in interrupts\n6  stranger asks anything sensitive → “sent to owner to approve”\n\nOUTBOUND TASK — make_call(“order a large pepperoni…”)\npre-flight: role · blocklist · unknown-number approval · quiet\nhours · caps · consent · $ budget · kill switch → dial w/ AsyncAMD\nAnsweredBy: human → converse · machine → ≤20 s voicemail after\nbeep · IVR → literal menu mode · fax/unknown → end + log\nalways: transcript + outcome + est. cost → ≤3-line owner summary\n\nLATENCY RULES (spec §7): first audio < 1 s · stream, never wait ·\nholding phrase on every tool call · 12 s timeout → graceful exit",
   "fontSize": 13,
   "fontFamily": 3,
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "middle",
   "containerId": "panelA",
   "originalText": "INBOUND CALL — LIFECYCLE\n1  caller dials your Twilio number\n2  Twilio POSTs /twilio/voice — S2 signature checked first\n3  caller ID → role → persona (owner: butler · stranger: front desk)\n4  TwiML <Connect><ConversationRelay url=wss://…?token=NONCE>\n5  WS accepted only with a fresh nonce (S9), then text↔text:\n    STT prompt in → brain tokens out → TTS · barge-in interrupts\n6  stranger asks anything sensitive → “sent to owner to approve”\n\nOUTBOUND TASK — make_call(“order a large pepperoni…”)\npre-flight: role · blocklist · unknown-number approval · quiet\nhours · caps · consent · $ budget · kill switch → dial w/ AsyncAMD\nAnsweredBy: human → converse · machine → ≤20 s voicemail after\nbeep · IVR → literal menu mode · fax/unknown → end + log\nalways: transcript + outcome + est. cost → ≤3-line owner summary\n\nLATENCY RULES (spec §7): first audio < 1 s · stream, never wait ·\nholding phrase on every tool call · 12 s timeout → graceful exit",
   "lineHeight": 1.25,
   "baseline": 13
  },
  {
   "id": "panelB",
